</div>
</div>
<p>Of the many and diverse Shinto shrines in existence, some are more well known:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Atsuta_Shrine" title="Atsuta Shrine">Atsuta Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nagoya" title="Nagoya">Nagoya</a>, shrine to the Imperial sword <a href="/wiki/Kusanagi" title="Kusanagi">Kusanagi</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Chichibu_Shrine" title="Chichibu Shrine">Chichibu Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Saitama_Prefecture" title="Saitama Prefecture">Saitama Prefecture</a>, dedicated to <a href="/wiki/Omoikane_(Shinto)" title="Omoikane (Shinto)">Omoikane</a> and <a href="/wiki/Amenominakanushi" title="Amenominakanushi">Amenominakanushi</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Heian_Jing%C5%AB" title="Heian Jingū" class="mw-redirect">Heian Jingū</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kyoto" title="Kyoto">Kyoto</a>, dedicated to <a href="/wiki/Emperor_Kammu" title="Emperor Kammu">Emperor Kammu</a> and <a href="/wiki/Emperor_K%C5%8Dmei" title="Emperor Kōmei">Emperor Kōmei</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hikawa_Shrine" title="Hikawa Shrine">Hikawa Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/%C5%8Cmiya-ku,_Saitama" title="Ōmiya-ku, Saitama">Omiya district</a></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Ise_Shrine" title="Ise Shrine">Grand Shrine of Ise</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ise,_Mie" title="Ise, Mie">Ise, Mie</a>, dedicated to <a href="/wiki/Amaterasu" title="Amaterasu">Amaterasu</a></li>
<li>The <a href="/w/index.php?title=Gassan_Hongu&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Gassan Hongu (page does not exist)">Gassan Hongu</a>, <a href="/wiki/Yamagata" title="Yamagata">Yamagata</a>, dedicated to <a href="/wiki/Tsukuyomi" title="Tsukuyomi">Tsukuyomi</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Itsukushima_Shrine" title="Itsukushima Shrine">Itsukushima Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hiroshima_Prefecture" title="Hiroshima Prefecture">Hiroshima Prefecture</a>, a <a href="/wiki/World_Heritage_Site" title="World Heritage Site">World Heritage Site</a> and one of the <a href="/wiki/National_Treasures_of_Japan" title="National Treasures of Japan">National Treasures of Japan</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Iwashimizu_Shrine" title="Iwashimizu Shrine" class="mw-redirect">Iwashimizu Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Yawata,_Kyoto" title="Yawata, Kyoto">Yawata, Kyoto</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Izumo_Taisha" title="Izumo Taisha">Izumo Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Izumo,_Shimane" title="Izumo, Shimane">Izumo</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Kasuga_Shrine" title="Kasuga Shrine">Kasuga Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nara,_Nara" title="Nara, Nara">Nara</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Katori_Shrine" title="Katori Shrine">Katori Shrine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Chiba_Prefecture" title="Chiba Prefecture">Chiba Prefecture</a>, dedicated to <a href="/wiki/Futsunushi" title="Futsunushi">Futsunushi</a></li>
<li>Kumano Shrines, <a href="/wiki/Wakayama_Prefecture" title="Wakayama Prefecture">Wakayama Prefecture</a></li>
